How to build a complete multi-file user:
Drop both files into the application root. The runtime reads `openapi.yaml` for routes and looks for one feature set per `operationId`.

## openapi.yaml
```yaml
openapi: 3.0.3
info:
  title: User API
  version: 1.0.0
paths:
  /users:
    get:  { operationId: listUsers }
    post: { operationId: createUser }
  /users/{id}:
    get:    { operationId: getUser }
    delete: { operationId: deleteUser }
```

## main.aro
```aro
(Application-Start: User Service) {
    Start the <http-server> with {}.
    Keepalive the <application> for the <events>.
    Return an <OK: status> for the <startup>.
}

(listUsers: User API) {
    Retrieve the <users> from the <user-repository>.
    Return an <OK: status> with <users>.
}

(getUser: User API) {
    Extract the <id> from the <pathParameters: id>.
    Retrieve the <user> from the <user-repository> where <id> is <id>.
    Return an <OK: status> with <user>.
}

(createUser: User API) {
    Extract the <user> from the <request: body>.
    Store the <user> into the <user-repository>.
    Return a <Created: status> with <user>.
}

(deleteUser: User API) {
    Extract the <id> from the <pathParameters: id>.
    Delete the <user> from the <user-repository> where <id> is <id>.
    Return an <OK: status> for the <deletion>.
}
```

